						               													<description>Dead Machine Gods is a strategic cyber-occult worker placement and tableau building mint tin game for 1-2 players. Set in a world of dark magic, occult technology, and haunted machinery.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gather resources, research and build arcane blueprints, and complete the rites of summoning to resurrect ancient mecha-deities. Will you appease the ancient ones or succumb to their grim will and embrace the call of annihilation?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each round of Dead Machine Gods, players will roll all their worker dice, and take turns placing workers on available card slots based-on their rolls. Placing workers lets you gather energy, material, and blueprints for building out your tableau.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when the first player completes their 8-card tableau (completing the rites of summoning). Players then tally the base victory points on the cards in their tableau as well any additional points earned form card abilities, placement synergies, and special symbols. The player with the highest score, wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
